            {
              "id": "SNYK-JAVA-CHQOSLOGBACK-13169722",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Medium severity - External Initialization of Trusted Variables or Data Stores vulnerability in ch.qos.logback:logback-core"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2025-11226) ch.qos.logback:logback-core@1.4.14"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Overview\n[ch.qos.logback:logback-core](https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/ch.qos.logback/logback-core) is a logback-core module.\n\nAffected versions of this package are vulnerable to External Initialization of Trusted Variables or Data Stores via the conditional processing of the `logback.xml` configuration file when both the Janino library and Spring Framework are present on the class path. An attacker can execute arbitrary code by compromising an existing configuration file or injecting a malicious environment variable before program execution. This is only exploitable if the attacker has write access to a configuration file or can set a malicious environment variable.\n## Remediation\nUpgrade `ch.qos.logback:logback-core` to version 1.3.16, 1.5.19 or higher.\n## References\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/qos-ch/logback/commit/61f6a2544f36b3016e0efd434ee21f19269f1df7)\n- [Release Notes](https://logback.qos.ch/news.html#1.3.16)\n- [Release Notes](https://logback.qos.ch/news.html#1.5.19)\n"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-454",
                  "maven"
                ],
                "cvssv3_baseScore": 5.9,
                "security-severity": "5.9"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "SNYK-JAVA-CHQOSLOGBACK-15062482",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Low severity - External Initialization of Trusted Variables or Data Stores vulnerability in ch.qos.logback:logback-core"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2026-1225) ch.qos.logback:logback-core@1.4.14"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Overview\n[ch.qos.logback:logback-core](https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/ch.qos.logback/logback-core) is a logback-core module.\n\nAffected versions of this package are vulnerable to External Initialization of Trusted Variables or Data Stores during the configuration file processing. An attacker can instantiate arbitrary classes already present on the class path by compromising an existing configuration file.\n## Remediation\nUpgrade `ch.qos.logback:logback-core` to version 1.5.25 or higher.\n## References\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/qos-ch/logback/commit/1f97ae1844b1be8486e4e9cade98d7123d3eded5)\n- [GitHub Issue](https://github.com/qos-ch/logback/issues/997)\n- [Logback Release Notes](https://logback.qos.ch/news.html#1.5.25)\n"
              },
